<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="199" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[173,660,1257,1729]" pageId="9" pageNumber="199">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,294,1496,1517]" pageId="9" pageNumber="199">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Spaeth, F." box="[301,447,1496,1517]" pageId="9" pageNumber="199" pagination="263 - 270" refId="ref16271" refString="Spaeth, F. 1932 b. Uber die mit Metriona erratica verwandten Arten (Col., Chrysom. Cass.). Folia Zoologica et Hydrobiologica 4 (2): 263 - 270." type="journal article" year="1932">Spaeth (1932b)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName box="[551,659,1496,1517]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Metrionella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="199" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bilimeki">
<emphasis box="[551,659,1496,1517]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="199">M. bilimeki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on a long series of specimens from various locations in Central America. However, he did not designate a 
<typeStatus box="[296,379,1576,1597]" pageId="9" pageNumber="199">holotype</typeStatus>
in the original description. 
<bibRefCitation author="Riley, E. G." box="[173,295,1602,1623]" pageId="9" pageNumber="199" pagination="98 - 114" refId="ref15289" refString="Riley, E. G. 1986. Review of the tortoise beetle genera of the tribe Cassidini occurring in America north of Mexico (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae: Cassidinae). Journal of the New York Entomological Society 94 (1): 98 - 114." type="journal article" year="1986">Riley (1986)</bibRefCitation>
studied the original type series in the MM and designated a male from 
<collectingCountry box="[494,596,1629,1650]" name="Guatemala" pageId="9" pageNumber="199">Guatemala</collectingCountry>
as the 
<typeStatus box="[173,263,1655,1676]" pageId="9" pageNumber="199">lectotype</typeStatus>
. The ZMH specimen originates from Spaeth’ s collection, is part of the type series, and thus is a 
<typeStatus box="[261,391,1708,1729]" pageId="9" pageNumber="199">paralectotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
